<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2399] Replace Stream.continually with Iterator.continually</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2399</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are two usages of `Stream.continually` and neither of them seems to need the extra functionality it provides over `Iterator.continually` (`Stream.continually` allocates `Cons` instances to save the computation instead of recomputing it if needed more than once).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12851179">KAFKA-2399</key>
